    assessment: "Specimen: serum. AST and ALT measured by rate of NADH consumption (kinetic assay). ALP measured by rate of p-nitrophenol production. Bilirubin measured by diazo reaction (Jendrassik-Grof method). Direct bilirubin reacts without accelerator; total bilirubin requires accelerator (caffeine-benzoate). Indirect bilirubin = total minus direct. Albumin measured by bromcresol green or bromcresol purple.",
    management: "Pattern recognition guides further workup: hepatocellular damage → viral hepatitis panel, autoimmune markers. Cholestatic pattern → imaging studies, GGT confirmation. Assess synthetic function with albumin, PT/INR. Monitor serial LFTs for disease progression or resolution.",
    complications: "Hemolysis interferes with bilirubin and AST measurements. Lipemia can interfere with spectrophotometric assays. Macroenzymes (macro-AST, macro-ALP) can cause persistently elevated results without true disease. Exercise can transiently elevate AST from skeletal muscle.",
