    overview: "Thyroid function tests evaluate the hypothalamic-pituitary-thyroid axis using TSH, free T4 (FT4), free T3 (FT3), total T4, and total T3. TSH is the most sensitive screening test for thyroid disorders. Immunoassay methods (chemiluminescent, electrochemiluminescent) are used for hormone quantitation. Understanding the negative feedback loop is essential for interpreting thyroid panels and identifying primary vs secondary thyroid dysfunction.",
